<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-1044] Changed behaviour of TestNG test execution after implementing runOrder support</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1044</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have some code automation around TestNG listeners. And I notice different behaviour of maven-surefire-plugin 2.15 and 2.16.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 2.15  In method  org.testng.TestNG.run during execution contains 1-XmlTestSuite with 1-XmlTest with 2 XmlClass inside. &lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ve also checked InteliJ org.testng.RemoteTestNG he has the same state during execution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But in 2.16 we have 2-XmlTestSuite with 1-XmlTest with 1 XmlClass inside. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a result TestNG initialise two IInvokedMethodListener instead of one. &lt;br/&gt;
Is this expected behaviour?&lt;br/&gt;
Example of test code I put here &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/skabashnyuk/mvntestng&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/skabashnyuk/mvntestng&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
